titleproper.value:
Archives of Irish America Material Culture Collection
                    <num>AIA.041</num>

author.value: Finding aid prepared by Rebecca Altermatt and Kaitlyn Medley

creation.value:
This finding aid was produced using the Archivists' Toolkit
                <date>2012-03-28T16:07-0400</date>

unittitle.value: Archives of Irish America Material Culture and Ephemera Collection

abstract.label: Abstract
abstract.value: The Archives of Irish America Material Culture collection is a conglomeration of objects individually donated or found in collections and removed.

p.value:
Published citations should take the following form: 
                <lb/>
                <lb/>Identification of item, date; Collection name; Collection number; box number; folder number; 
                <lb/>Archives of Irish America, Tamiment Library 
                <lb/>Elmer Holmes Bobst Library 
                <lb/>70 Washington Square South 
                <lb/>New York, NY 10012, New York University Libraries.

The Material Culture collection compliments the entire Archives of Irish America in that its contents ... The unique format of many of the materials - hats, t-shirts, bumper stickers - provide insight to scholars and researchers in the methods used to convey information within the Irish-American community.

The collection consists of a variety of items such as buttons, bumper stickers, hats, tickets, membership cards, pens, pins, and t-shirts -- many of them related to Irish organizations. Contents of the collection came in as individual accessions or as part of larger accessions, including the Dorothy Hayden Cudahy Irish Memories Collection, and were organized together into this artificial collection.
